    "description": [
        "Episode of Series \"Chemistry\". Illustrates the chemical nature of a solution, what happens when it forms and the role of the electrostatic forces. Shows Brownian movement, defines saturation and presents the concept of molarity along with an explanation of why some substances, eg oil, won't dissolve in other substances such as water. Suitable for upper secondary level."
